(249, 1, '2019-09-13 07:16:12', '2019-09-13 07:16:12', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Problem?</strong><br><br><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\n2</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I failed to run&nbsp;<code>node-sass</code>(node module), where I was able to setup path for input&nbsp;<code>extensions.scss</code>files and output files generated after compiling to&nbsp;<code>dist/</code>&nbsp;folder.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now, I am using vscode extension&nbsp;<code>live sass compiler</code>,</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>at bottom bar, when I clicked&nbsp;<code>Watched Sass</code>&nbsp;then it compiled automatically&nbsp;<code>scss</code>&nbsp;file to&nbsp;<code>css</code>&nbsp;but in same folder.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><code>main.scss</code>&nbsp;is compiled to&nbsp;<code>main.css</code>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><a href=\"https://i.stack.imgur.com/w1A29.png\"><img src=\"https://i.stack.imgur.com/w1A29.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"/></a></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>problem is that I wanted to create that&nbsp;<code>compiled css</code>&nbsp;file in other folder .i.e. in output folder&nbsp;<code>./dist/</code>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I have manually created&nbsp;<code>main.css</code>&nbsp;file in&nbsp;<code>./dist/folder</code>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>How can I setup path to source and destination files in that extension?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Solutions</strong><br><br><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I have had the same issue when I started implementing SMACSS methodology to my projects. This is the solution I have tried. hope it will help you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><a href=\"https://i.stack.imgur.com/yvHPe.png\"><img src=\"https://i.stack.imgur.com/yvHPe.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"/></a></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Go to VScode User Settings --&gt; Select \"Live Sass Compiler Config --&gt; add</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>\"liveSassCompile.settings.formats\": [{\n        \"format\": \"expanded\",\n        \"extensionName\": \".css\",\n        \"savePath\": \"./css\"\n    }]\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><a href=\"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Gho7y.png\"><img src=\"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Gho7y.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"/></a><figcaption><br></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MORE DETAILS https://stackoverflow.com/questions/51696892/how-to-setup-output-path-to-compiled-css-files-using-vscode-live-sass-compiler<br><br>or on Visual Studio code<br><br>https://github.com/ritwickdey/vscode-live-sass-compiler/blob/master/docs/settings.md</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>https://github.com/ritwickdey/vscode-live-sass-compiler/blob/master/docs/settings.md</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>CORRECTIONS</strong><br><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\n{    \"liveServer.settings.donotVerifyTags\": true,    \"workbench.editor.highlightModifiedTabs\": true,    \"editor.wordWrap\": \"on\",            \"liveSassCompile.settings.formats\": [{        \"format\": \"compressed\",        \"extensionName\": \".css\",        \"savePath\": \"./css\"    }],\"explorer.confirmDelete\": false<br>}\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'How to setup output path to compiled css files using `vscode live sass compiler extension` in windows10?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-09-13 07:16:12', '2019-09-13 07:16:12', '', 172, 'https://www.ayushshrestha.com.np/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(250, 1, '2019-09-13 08:16:33', '2019-09-13 08:16:33', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Problem?</strong><br><br><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\n2</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I failed to run&nbsp;<code>node-sass</code>(node module), where I was able to setup path for input&nbsp;<code>extensions.scss</code>files and output files generated after compiling to&nbsp;<code>dist/</code>&nbsp;folder.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now, I am using vscode extension&nbsp;<code>live sass compiler</code>,</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>at bottom bar, when I clicked&nbsp;<code>Watched Sass</code>&nbsp;then it compiled automatically&nbsp;<code>scss</code>&nbsp;file to&nbsp;<code>css</code>&nbsp;but in same folder.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><code>main.scss</code>&nbsp;is compiled to&nbsp;<code>main.css</code>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><a href=\"https://i.stack.imgur.com/w1A29.png\"><img src=\"https://i.stack.imgur.com/w1A29.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"/></a></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>problem is that I wanted to create that&nbsp;<code>compiled css</code>&nbsp;file in other folder .i.e. in output folder&nbsp;<code>./dist/</code>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I have manually created&nbsp;<code>main.css</code>&nbsp;file in&nbsp;<code>./dist/folder</code>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>How can I setup path to source and destination files in that extension?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Solutions</strong><br><br><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I have had the same issue when I started implementing SMACSS methodology to my projects. This is the solution I have tried. hope it will help you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><a href=\"https://i.stack.imgur.com/yvHPe.png\"><img src=\"https://i.stack.imgur.com/yvHPe.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"/></a></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Go to VScode User Settings --&gt; Select \"Live Sass Compiler Config --&gt; add</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>\"liveSassCompile.settings.formats\": [{\n        \"format\": \"expanded\",\n        \"extensionName\": \".css\",\n        \"savePath\": \"./css\"\n    }]\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><a href=\"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Gho7y.png\"><img src=\"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Gho7y.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"/></a><figcaption><br></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MORE DETAILS https://stackoverflow.com/questions/51696892/how-to-setup-output-path-to-compiled-css-files-using-vscode-live-sass-compiler<br><br>or on Visual Studio code<br><br>https://github.com/ritwickdey/vscode-live-sass-compiler/blob/master/docs/settings.md</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>https://github.com/ritwickdey/vscode-live-sass-compiler/blob/master/docs/settings.md</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>CORRECTIONS</strong><br><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n{\n    \"liveServer.settings.donotVerifyTags\": true,\n    \"workbench.editor.highlightModifiedTabs\": true,\n    \"editor.wordWrap\": \"on\",\n    \n    \n    \"liveSassCompile.settings.formats\": [{\n        \"format\": \"compressed\",\n        \"extensionName\": \".css\",\n        \"savePath\": \"./css\"\n    }\n],\n\"explorer.confirmDelete\": false\n\n}\n<!-- /wp:html -->', 'How to setup output path to compiled css files using `vscode live sass compiler extension` in windows10?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-09-13 08:16:33', '2019-09-13 08:16:33', '', 172, 'https://www.ayushshrestha.com.np/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(252, 1, '2019-12-14 09:39:27', '2019-12-14 09:39:27', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>while you add chatbot message box in your website it it didnt work if you check console and it says that </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":253} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.ayushshrestha.com.np/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/image-1024x85.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-253\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Refused to display \'https://www.facebook.com/v2.12/plugins/customerchat.php?app_id=&amp;attribution=setup_tool&amp;channel=https%3A%2F%2Fstaticxx.facebook.com%2Fconnect%2Fxd_arbiter.php%3Fversion%3D44%23cb%3Df13ed322c49f5e%26domain%3Dwww.floristnepal.com%26origin%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.floristnepal.com%252Ff173aec3cd4b68%26relation%3Dparent.parent&amp;container_width=0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;page_id=398777027226348&amp;sdk=joey\' in a frame because an ancestor violates the following Content Security Policy directive: \"frame-ancestors https://www.facebook.com\".<br> about:blank:1 Refused to display \'https://www.facebook.com/v2.12/plugins/customerchat.php?app_id=&amp;attribution=setup_tool&amp;channel=https%3A%2F%2Fstaticxx.facebook.com%2Fconnect%2Fxd_arbiter.php%3Fversion%3D44%23cb%3Df13ed322c49f5e%26domain%3Dwww.floristnepal.com%26origin%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.floristnepal.com%252Ff173aec3cd4b68%26relation%3Dparent.parent&amp;container_width=0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;page_id=398777027226348&amp;sdk=joey\' in a frame because an ancestor violates the following Content Security Policy directive: \"frame-ancestors https://www.facebook.com\".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>SOLUTION</strong> :</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You should whitelist your domain https://developers.facebook.com/docs/messenger-platform/messenger-profile/domain-whitelisting</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragra